data.description: 2BD/2BA house with great curb appeal and lush landscaping that leads to the upgraded front door which opens up to a formal living and dining rooms.  Dining room has a lovely fixture. The  kitchen has a time saving dishwasher, refrigerator, clear top range and built-in microwave. It has a wonderful eat-in area  Master bedroom has tray ceiling, separate walk-in closets, a reach in closet and plenty of room for a king size bed. Master bathroom has double sink vanity with plenty of storage, soaking tub and walk-in shower. Guest bedroom has ceiling fan and a full-length closet. Guest bathroom has vanity with lots of storage, walk-in shower and a linen closet. Family room is located just off the kitchen area and has room for a big screen television. Covered  Outside Patio. Ideal location: Shopping across the street includes Publix, Walgreens, various Restaurants, Banks, Drug store, McDonalds, etc. 1.5 East of the World Equestrian Center. 1 ½ hours from each Coast. 1 ½ hours from Disney World, Epcot, Universal Studios, Sea World, etc. All measurements are approximate – Buyer(s) to re-measure.
